.TH "GEOIP" 7 "February 2026" "atomdns handlers" "atomdns authors"

.SH "NAME"
.PP
\fIgeoip\fP \- add geographical location data

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The \fIgeoip\fP handler adds geographical location data associated with the client IP. You can install a database
on Debian systems with \fB\fCapt-get install geoip-database\fR, or see https://mailfud.org/geoip\-legacy/.

.PP
There is no automatic reloading of the databases under the assumption they will not change \fIthat\fP often.

.PP
If an IP address does not have associated geographical location data, nothing is added to the context. If the
\fIecs\fP handler is active and has added data to the context the address from there is used instead of the
sources address of the query.

.SH "SYNTAX"
.PP
.RS

.nf
geoip {
    city DBFILE4 [DBFILE6]
    asn DBFILE4 [DBFILE6]
}

.fi
.RE

.IP \(bu 4
\fB\fCcity\fR and \fB\fCasn\fR define the database files that should be used for country, city or AS number
lookups. If the path is relative the path from \fB\fCroot\fR will be prepended. At least one database must be
loaded.


.SH "CONTEXT"
.PP
The following values will be stored in the context of a request and can be used by other handlers.

.PP
The continent codes are: \fB\fCAF\fR: Africa, \fB\fCAN\fR: Antarctica, \fB\fCAS\fR: Asia, \fB\fCEU\fR: Europe, \fB\fCNA\fR: North America,
\fB\fCOC\fR: Oceania, \fB\fCSA\fR: South America.

.RS
.TS
allbox;
