.
\fBKey\fP\fB	Type\fP\fB	Example\fP\fB	Description\fP
\fB\fCgeoip/city\fR	\fB\fCstring\fR	Cambridge	The city name in English language.
\fB\fCgeoip/city/region\fR	\fB\fC[]string\fR	ENG TWH	Regional ISO 3166\-2 codes.
\fB\fCgeoip/country\fR	\fB\fCstring\fR	GB	Country ISO 3166\-1 code.
\fB\fCgeoip/country/eu\fR	\fB\fCbool\fR	false	Country is EU member.
\fB\fCgeoip/continent\fR	\fB\fCstring\fR	EU	Continent code.
\fB\fCgeoip/latitude\fR	\fB\fCfloat64\fR	52.2242	Base 10, max available precision.
\fB\fCgeoip/longitude\fR	\fB\fCfloat64\fR	0.1315	Base 10, max available precision.
\fB\fCgeoip/timezone\fR	\fB\fCstring\fR	Europe/London	The time zone.
\fB\fCgeoip/asn\fR	\fB\fCint\fR	37	The AS number.
\fB\fCgeoip/asn/organization\fR	\fB\fCstring\fR	Example Org	The AS organization.
.TE
.RE


.SH "EXAMPLE"
.PP
Here we add location data to the request's context, so that \fItemplate\fP can use it in the template creation.

.PP
.RS

.nf
example.org. {
    geoip {
        city testdata/GeoIPCity.dat
    }

    template .* {
        mytemplate.go.tmpl
    }
}

.fi
.RE

